    "165104010373974e3d": {
      "type": "section-accordions",
      "blocks": {
        "1651040103e3874ae9-1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does this product come with a warranty?",
            "text": "<p>All our products are subject to quality control.<br/><br/>Our warranty provides a guarantee against manufacturer defects.<br/><br/>The guarantee covers any manufacturing, design, or material defect. Please notify us within 2 months of noticing any defects.<br/><br/>It does not cover blows, improper use, or other issues that are not attributable to a manufacturer defects.</p>"
          }
        },
        "43df9585-9879-41aa-96c3-cf9705d2fb9a": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How durable are the materials used?",
            "text": "<p>Utility bags are typically made of strong, durable materials such as canvas, nylon, and leather. They are designed to handle daily wear and tear, so they should last for many years proper care and maintenance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "71da687a-5e3d-4655-b29c-94a53f8134b6": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Are these bags drop-proof?",
            "text": "<p>Yes, our bags are usually made of tough and durable materials, like Kevlar and ballistic nylon, that can withstand impacts and shock. They also have reinforced seams and zippers to prevent the contents from spilling.</p>"
          }
        },
        "732e74c0-f3f8-4fcb-8d61-6a44af68845e": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What kind of padding is used in the bags?",
            "text": "<p>Utility bags usually have some form of cushioning or padding in them to protect the items inside. Foam padding and filler material are both commonly used. The thickness of the padding can vary depending on the type of bag and its intended use.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
